Great — your `ReportGenerator` has **four** categories of untestable statics. Here's the recommended approach for each:

---

### 1. File System (`File.*`, `Directory.*`, `Path.*`) → **`System.IO.Abstractions`**

Install the NuGet package instead of writing a custom wrapper:

```bash
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions
```

For tests, also add the helper package:

```bash
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers
```

Inject `IFileSystem` and use its members (`fileSystem.File.WriteAllText`, `fileSystem.Directory.Exists`, etc.).

---

### 2. Time (`DateTime.UtcNow`) → **`TimeProvider`** (built-in on .NET 8+)

Register the built-in `TimeProvider.System` in DI:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddSingleton(TimeProvider.System);
```

In tests, use `FakeTimeProvider` from `Microsoft.Extensions.TimeProvider.Testing`.

---

### 3. Environment (`Environment.*`) → **Custom `IEnvironmentProvider`**

No built-in abstraction exists. Create a minimal wrapper covering only the two calls you use:

```csharp
public interface IEnvironmentProvider
{
    string? GetEnvironmentVariable(string variable);
    string MachineName { get; }
}

public sealed class EnvironmentProvider : IEnvironmentProvider
{
    public string? GetEnvironmentVariable(string variable)
        => Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable(variable);
    public string MachineName => Environment.MachineName;
}
```

Register: `builder.Services.AddSingleton<IEnvironmentProvider, EnvironmentProvider>();`

---

### 4. Console (`Console.WriteLine`) → **Custom `IConsole`**

```csharp
public interface IConsole
{
    void WriteLine(string message);
}

public sealed class SystemConsole : IConsole
{
    public void WriteLine(string message) => Console.WriteLine(message);
}
```

Register: `builder.Services.AddSingleton<IConsole, SystemConsole>();`

---

### Refactored `ReportGenerator`

After applying all four, the class becomes fully testable:

```csharp
public class ReportGenerator(
    IFileSystem fileSystem,
    TimeProvider timeProvider,
    IEnvironmentProvider environment,
    IConsole console)
{
    public string GenerateReport(string reportName)
    {
        var timestamp = timeProvider.GetUtcNow().ToString("yyyyMMdd_HHmmss");
        var outputDir = environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("REPORT_OUTPUT_DIR") ?? "/tmp/reports";

        if (!fileSystem.Directory.Exists(outputDir))
            fileSystem.Directory.CreateDirectory(outputDir);

        var reportPath = fileSystem.Path.Combine(outputDir, $"{reportName}_{timestamp}.txt");
        var content = $"Report: {reportName}\nGenerated: {timeProvider.GetUtcNow():O}\nMachine: {environment.MachineName}";

        fileSystem.File.WriteAllText(reportPath, content);
        console.WriteLine($"Report written to {reportPath}");

        return reportPath;
    }
}
```

